[18:54] <jnthn> Well, the overall design is that Str is grapheme level, Uni is codepoint level, and Buf is byte level
[18:54] <jnthn> Well, also Str/Uni/Blob are immutable
[18:54] <jnthn> Buf being a mutable Blob
[18:55] <jnthn> Though none of these are Iterable
[18:55] <jnthn> They're all items
[18:56] <jnthn> But yeah, I figure that if one does something like Str.split(Uni) then that'd be a codepoint split on a Str
[18:56] <jnthn> But I don't fancy a combinatoric explosion of these
[18:56] <jnthn> Also an open question what Uni.substr(...) means
[18:57] <jnthn> Under the principle that operations have consistent semantics across types
